#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:278(para)
msgid ""
"This section introduces some common ways to determine the cause if problems "
"arise."
msgstr ""
"Esta sección introduce algunas maneras comunes de determinar la causa si se "
"presentan problemas."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:282(title)
msgid "Escaping chroot"
msgstr "Saliendo de chroot"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:283(para)
msgid ""
"The Ubuntu <application>postfix</application> package will by default "
"install into a <emphasis>chroot</emphasis> environment for security reasons. "
"This can add greater complexity when troubleshooting problems."
msgstr ""
"El paquete <application>postfix</application> de Ubuntu se instalara por "
"defecto en un ambiente <emphasis>chroot</emphasis> por medidas de seguridad. "
"Esto puede añadir mayor complejidad cuando se resuelvan problemas."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:287(para)
msgid ""
"To turn off the chroot operation locate for the following line in the "
"<filename>/etc/postfix/master.cf</filename> configuration file:"
msgstr ""
"Para apagar la operación chroot , busque la siguiente línea en el archivo de "
"configuración <filename>/etc/postfix/master.cf</filename>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:291(screen)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"smtp      inet  n       -       -       -       -       smtpd\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"smtp      inet  n       -       -       -       -       smtpd\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:294(para)
msgid "and modify it as follows:"
msgstr "y modifíquelo de esta forma:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:297(screen)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"smtp      inet  n       -       n       -       -       smtpd\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"smtp      inet  n       -       n       -       -       smtpd\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:300(para)
msgid ""
"You will then need to restart Postfix to use the new configuration. From a "
"terminal prompt enter:"
msgstr ""
"Necesitará reiniciar Postfix para usar la nueva configuración. En una "
"consola teclee:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:308(title)
msgid "Log Files"
msgstr "Archivos log"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:309(para)
msgid ""
"<application>Postfix</application> sends all log messages to "
"<filename>/var/log/mail.log</filename>. However error and warning messages "
"can sometimes get lost in the normal log output so they are also logged to "
"<filename>/var/log/mail.err</filename> and "
"<filename>/var/log/mail.warn</filename> respectively."
msgstr ""
"<application>Postfix</application> envía todos los mensajes de registro a "
"<filename>/var/log/mail.log</filename>. Sin embargo, algunas veces, los "
"mensajes de error y advertencia pueden perderse en la salida normal de "
"registro y, por esta razón, también se registran en "
"<filename>/var/log/mail.err</filename> y "
"<filename>/var/log/mail.warn</filename> respectivamente."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:314(para)
msgid ""
"To see messages entered into the logs in real time you can use the "
"<application>tail -f</application> command:"
msgstr ""
"Para ver los mensajes ingresados en los registros en tiempo real usted puede "
"utilizar el comando <application>tail -f</application>:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:319(command)
msgid "tail -f /var/log/mail.err"
msgstr "tail -f /var/log/mail.err"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:321(para)
msgid ""
"The amount of detail that is recorded in the logs can be increased. Below "
"are some configuration options for increasing the log level for some of the "
"areas covered above."
msgstr ""
"La cantidad de detalles que se graba en los registros puede ser aumentada. A "
"continuación hay algunas opciones de configuración para aumentar el nivel de "
"registro para algunas de las áreas cubiertas anteriormente."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:327(para)
msgid ""
"To increase <emphasis>TLS</emphasis> activity logging set the "
"<emphasis>smtpd_tls_loglevel</emphasis> option to a value from 1 to 4."
msgstr ""
"Para incrementar la actividad de registro de TLS ponga la opción "
"<emphasis>smtpd_tls_loglevel</emphasis> a un valor entre 1 y 4."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:331(command)
msgid "sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_loglevel = 4'"
msgstr "sudo postconf -e 'smtpd_tls_loglevel = 4'"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:335(para)
msgid ""
"If you are having trouble sending or receiving mail from a specific domain "
"you can add the domain to the <emphasis>debug_peer_list</emphasis> parameter."
msgstr ""
"Si usted tiene problema enviando o recibiendo correo de un dominio "
"específico, usted puede agregar el dominio al parámetro "
"<emphasis>debug_peer_list</emphasis>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:340(command)
msgid "sudo postconf -e 'debug_peer_list = problem.domain'"
msgstr "sudo postconf -e 'debug_peer_list = problem.domain'"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:344(para)
msgid ""
"You can increase the verbosity of any <application>Postfix</application> "
"daemon process by editing the <filename>/etc/postfix/master.cf</filename> "
"and adding a <emphasis>-v</emphasis> after the entry. For example edit the "
"<emphasis>smtp</emphasis> entry:"
msgstr ""
"Puede incrementar la elocuencia de cualquier proceso "
"<application>Postfix</application> editando el "
"<filename>/etc/postfix/master.cf</filename> y añadiendo <emphasis>-"
"v</emphasis> luego de la entrada. Por ejemplo edite la entrada "
"<emphasis>smtp</emphasis>:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:348(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"smtp      unix  -       -       -       -       -       smtp -v\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"smtp      unix  -       -       -       -       -       smtp -v\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:354(para)
msgid ""
"It is important to note that after making one of the logging changes above "
"the <application>Postfix</application> process will need to be reloaded in "
"order to recognize the new configuration: <command>sudo /etc/init.d/postfix "
"reload</command>"
msgstr ""
"Es importante notar que después de hacer los cambios de registro anteriores, "
"el proceso de <application>Postfix</application> necesitara ser recargado a "
"fin de reconocer la nueva configuración: <command>sudo /etc/init.d/postfix "
"reload</command>"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:361(para)
msgid ""
"To increase the amount of information logged when troubleshooting "
"<emphasis>SASL</emphasis> issues you can set the following options in "
"<filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename>"
msgstr ""
"Para incrementar la cantidad de información registrada cuando se localiza un "
"problema <emphasis>SASL</emphasis> puede establecer las opciones siguientes "
"en <filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename>"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:365(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"auth_debug=yes\n"
"auth_debug_passwords=yes\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"auth_debug=yes\n"
"auth_debug_passwords=yes\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:372(para)
msgid ""
"Just like <application>Postfix</application> if you change a "
"<application>Dovecot</application> configuration the process will need to be "
"reloaded: <command>sudo /etc/init.d/dovecot reload</command>."
msgstr ""
"Asi como en <application>Postfix</application>, si usted cambia una "
"configuracion de <application>Dovecot</application>, el proceso necesitara "
"ser recargado: <command>sudo /etc/init.d/dovecot reload</command>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:378(para)
msgid ""
"Some of the options above can drastically increase the amount of information "
"sent to the log files. Remember to return the log level back to normal after "
"you have corrected the problem. Then reload the appropriate daemon for the "
"new configuration to take affect."
msgstr ""
"Alguna de las opciones anteriores puede incrementar drásticamente la "
"cantidad de información enviada a los archivos de registro. Recuerde "
"retornar el nivel de registro de vuelta a normal después de que usted haya "
"corregido el problema. Luego recargue el demonio apropiada para que la nueva "
"configuración haga efecto."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:386(para)
msgid ""
"Administering a <application>Postfix</application> server can be a very "
"complicated task. At some point you may need to turn to the Ubuntu community "
"for more experienced help."
msgstr ""
"Administrar un servidor <application>Postfix</application> puede ser una "
"tarea complicada. En algún punto puede que deba dirigirse a la comunidad de "
"Ubuntu para ayuda más experimentada."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:390(para)
msgid ""
"A great place to ask for <application>Postfix</application> assistance, and "
"get involved with the Ubuntu Server community, is the <emphasis>#ubuntu-"
"server</emphasis> IRC channel on <ulink "
"url=\"http://freenode.net\">freenode</ulink>. You can also post a message to "
"one of the <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/support/community/webforums\">Web Forums</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Un gran lugar para solicitar ayuda sobre <application>Postfix</application>, "
"y relacionarse con la comunidad de Ubuntu Server, es el canal IRC "
"<emphasis>#ubuntu-server</emphasis> en <ulink "
"url=\"http://freenode.net\">freenode</ulink>. Usted también puede poner un "
"mensaje en alguno de los <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/support/community/webforums\">Foros Web</ulink>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:395(para)
msgid ""
"For in depth <application>Postfix</application> information Ubuntu "
"developers highly recommend: <ulink url=\"http://www.postfix-book.com/\">The "
"Book of Postfix</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Para información más a fondo de <application>Postfix</application> los "
"desarrolladores de Ubuntu recomiendan altamente: <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.postfix-book.com/\">The Book of Postfix</ulink>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:399(para)
msgid ""
"Finally, the <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.postfix.org/documentation.html\">Postfix</ulink> website "
"also has great documentation on all the different configuration options "
"available."
msgstr ""
"Finalmente el sitio web de <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.postfix.org/documentation.html\">Postfix</ulink> también "
"tiene mucha documentación sobre todas las diferentes opciones de "
"configuración disponibles."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:408(title) serverguide/C/mail.xml:753(title) serverguide/C/mail.xml:869(title)
msgid "Exim4"
msgstr "Exim4"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:409(para)
msgid ""
"<application>Exim4</application> is another Message Transfer Agent (MTA) "
"developed at the University of Cambridge for use on Unix systems connected "
"to the Internet. Exim can be installed in place of "
"<application>sendmail</application>, although the configuration of "
"<application>exim</application> is quite different to that of "
"<application>sendmail</application>."
msgstr ""
"<application>Exim4</application> es otro Agente de Transferencia de Mensajes "
"(MTA) desarrollado en la universidad de Cambridge para usarse en sistemas "
"Unix conectados a la Internet. Exim puede instalarse en lugar de "
"<application>sendmail</application>, aunque la configuración de "
"<application>exim</application> es un poco diferente a la de "
"<application>sendmail</application>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:420(para)
msgid ""
"To install <application>exim4</application>, run the following command: "
"<screen>\n"
"<command>sudo apt-get install exim4</command>\n"
"</screen>"
msgstr ""
"Para instalar <application>exim4</application>, ejecute la siguiente orden: "
"<screen>\n"
"<command>sudo apt-get install exim4</command>\n"
"</screen>"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:429(para)
msgid ""
"To configure <application>Exim4</application>, run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:433(command)
msgid "sudo dpkg-reconfigure exim4-config"
msgstr "sudo dpkg-reconfigure exim4-config"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:435(para)
msgid ""
"The user interface will be displayed. The user interface lets you configure "
"many parameters. For example, In <application>Exim4</application> the "
"configuration files are split among multiple files. If you wish to have them "
"in one file you can configure accordingly in this user interface."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:443(para)
msgid ""
"All the parameters you configure in the user interface are stored in "
"<filename>/etc/exim4/update-exim4.conf.conf</filename> file. If you wish to "
"re-configure, either you re-run the configuration wizard or manually edit "
"this file using your favourite editor. Once you configure, you can run the "
"following command to generate the master configuration file:"
msgstr ""
"Todos los parámetros que usted configure en la interfaz de usuario son "
"almacenados en el archivo <filename>/etc/exim4/update-"
"exim4.conf.conf</filename>. Si usted desea reconfigurar, puede reejecutar el "
"asistente de configuración o editar manualmente este archivo utilizando su "
"editor favorito. Una vez que configure, usted puede ejecutar el siguiente "
"comando para generar el archivo de configuración maestro."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:454(command) serverguide/C/mail.xml:527(command)
msgid "sudo update-exim4.conf"
msgstr "sudo update-exim4.conf"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:456(para)
msgid ""
"The master configuration file, is generated and it is stored in "
"<filename>/var/lib/exim4/config.autogenerated</filename>."
msgstr ""
"El archivo de configuración maestro se genera y se almacena en "
"<filename>/var/lib/exim4/config.autogenerated</filename>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:462(para)
msgid ""
"At any time, you should not edit the master configuration file, "
"<filename>/var/lib/exim4/config.autogenerated</filename> manually. It is "
"updated automatically every time you run <command>update-exim4.conf</command>"
msgstr ""
"En cualquier caso, no debería editar manualmente el archivo de configuración "
"principal, <filename>/var/lib/exim4/config.autogenerated</filename>. Éste se "
"actualiza automáticamente cada vez que se ejecuta la orden <command>update-"
"exim4.conf</command>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:470(para)
msgid ""
"You can run the following command to start <application>Exim4</application> "
"daemon."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:475(command) serverguide/C/mail.xml:875(command)
msgid "sudo /etc/init.d/exim4 start"
msgstr "sudo /etc/init.d/exim4 start"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:480(para)
msgid ""
"This section covers configuring Exim4 to use SMTP-AUTH with TLS and SASL."
msgstr ""
"Esta sección cubre la configuración de Exim4 para utilizar SMTP-AUTH con TLS "
"y SASL."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:483(para)
msgid ""
"The first step is to create a certificate for use with TLS. Enter the "
"following into a terminal prompt:"
msgstr ""
"El primer paso es crear un certificado para su uso con TLS. Introduzca lo "
"siguiente en un terminal:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:487(command)
msgid "sudo /usr/share/doc/exim4-base/examples/exim-gencert"
msgstr "sudo /usr/share/doc/exim4-base/examples/exim-gencert"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:489(para)
msgid ""
"Now Exim4 needs to be configured for TLS by editing "
"<filename>/etc/exim4/conf.d/main/03_exim4-config_tlsoptions</filename> add "
"the following:"
msgstr ""
"Ahora Exim4 necesita ser configura para TLS editando "
"<filename>/etc/exim4/conf.d/main/03_exim4-config_tlsoptions</filename>, "
"agregue lo siguiente:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:493(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"MAIN_TLS_ENABLE = yes\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"MAIN_TLS_ENABLE = yes\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:496(para)
msgid ""
"Next you need to configure <application>Exim4</application> to use the "
"<application>saslauthd</application> for authentication. Edit "
"<filename>/etc/exim4/conf.d/auth/30_exim4-config_examples</filename> and "
"uncomment the <emphasis>plain_saslauthd_server</emphasis> and "
"<emphasis>login_saslauthd_server</emphasis> sections:"
msgstr ""
"Luego necesita configurar <application>Exim4</application> para usar "
"<application>saslauthd</application> para autenticarte. Edite "
"<filename>/etc/exim4/conf.d/auth/30_exim4-config_examples</filename> y de-"
"comente las secciones <emphasis>plain_saslauthd_server</emphasis> y "
"<emphasis>login_saslauthd_server</emphasis>:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:501(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
" plain_saslauthd_server:\n"
"   driver = plaintext\n"
"   public_name = PLAIN\n"
"   server_condition = ${if saslauthd{{$auth2}{$auth3}}{1}{0}}\n"
"   server_set_id = $auth2\n"
"   server_prompts = :\n"
"   .ifndef AUTH_SERVER_ALLOW_NOTLS_PASSWORDS\n"
"   server_advertise_condition = ${if eq{$tls_cipher}{}{}{*}}\n"
"   .endif\n"
"#\n"
" login_saslauthd_server:\n"
"   driver = plaintext\n"
"   public_name = LOGIN\n"
"   server_prompts = \"Username:: : Password::\"\n"
"   # don't send system passwords over unencrypted connections\n"
"   server_condition = ${if saslauthd{{$auth1}{$auth2}}{1}{0}}\n"
"   server_set_id = $auth1\n"
"   .ifndef AUTH_SERVER_ALLOW_NOTLS_PASSWORDS\n"
"   server_advertise_condition = ${if eq{$tls_cipher}{}{}{*}}\n"
"   .endif\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
" plain_saslauthd_server:\n"
"   driver = plaintext\n"
"   public_name = PLAIN\n"
"   server_condition = ${if saslauthd{{$auth2}{$auth3}}{1}{0}}\n"
"   server_set_id = $auth2\n"
"   server_prompts = :\n"
"   .ifndef AUTH_SERVER_ALLOW_NOTLS_PASSWORDS\n"
"   server_advertise_condition = ${if eq{$tls_cipher}{}{}{*}}\n"
"   .endif\n"
"#\n"
" login_saslauthd_server:\n"
"   driver = plaintext\n"
"   public_name = LOGIN\n"
"   server_prompts = \"Usuario:: : Contraseña::\"\n"
"   # No envié contraseñas del sistema sobre conexiones no encriptadas\n"
"   server_condition = ${if saslauthd{{$auth1}{$auth2}}{1}{0}}\n"
"   server_set_id = $auth1\n"
"   .ifndef AUTH_SERVER_ALLOW_NOTLS_PASSWORDS\n"
"   server_advertise_condition = ${if eq{$tls_cipher}{}{}{*}}\n"
"   .endif\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:523(para)
msgid "Finally, update the Exim4 configuration and restart the service:"
msgstr "Finalmente actualice la configuración Exim4 y reinicie el servicio:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:528(command)
msgid "sudo /etc/init.d/exim4 restart"
msgstr "sudo /etc/init.d/exim4 restart"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:533(para)
msgid ""
"This section provides details on configuring the saslauthd to provide "
"authentication for <application>Exim4</application>."
msgstr ""
"Esta sección proporciona detalles sobre la configuración de saslauthd para "
"proporcionar autenticación para <application>Exim4</application>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:536(para)
msgid ""
"The first step is to install the sasl2-bin package. From a terminal prompt "
"enter the following:"
msgstr ""
"El primer paso es instalar el paquete sasl2-bin. En un terminal teclee lo "
"siguiente:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:540(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install sasl2-bin"
msgstr "sudo apt-get install sasl2-bin"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:542(para)
msgid ""
"To configure saslauthd edit the /etc/default/saslauthd configuration file "
"and set START=no to:"
msgstr ""
"Para configurar saslauthd, edite el archivo de configuración "
"/etc/default/saslauthd y coloque START=no a:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:545(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"START=yes\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"START=yes\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:548(para)
msgid ""
"Next the <emphasis>Debian-exim</emphasis> user needs to be part of the "
"<emphasis>sasl</emphasis> group in order for Exim4 to use the saslauthd "
"service:"
msgstr ""
"Seguidamente el usuario <emphasis>Debian-exim</emphasis> necesita ser parte "
"del grupo <emphasis>sasl</emphasis> para que Exim4 pueda usar el servicio "
"saslauthd:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:553(command)
msgid "sudo adduser Debian-exim sasl"
msgstr "sudo adduser Debian-exim sasl"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:555(para)
msgid "Now start the <application>saslauthd</application> service:"
msgstr "Ahora inicie el servicio <application>saslauthd</application>:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:559(command)
msgid "sudo /etc/init.d/saslauthd start"
msgstr "sudo /etc/init.d/saslauthd start"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:561(para)
msgid ""
"<application>Exim4</application> is now configured with SMTP-AUTH using TLS "
"and SASL authentication."
msgstr ""
"<application>Exim4</application> está ahora configurada con SMTP-AUTH usando "
"autenticación TLS y SASL."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:567(title)
msgid "Dovecot Server"
msgstr "Servidor Dovecot"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:568(para)
msgid ""
"<application>Dovecot</application> is a Mail Delivery Agent, written with "
"security primarily in mind. It supports the major mailbox formats: mbox or "
"Maildir. This section explain how to set it up as an imap or pop3 server."
msgstr ""
"<application>Dovecot</application> es un Agente de Entrega de Correo, "
"escrito con la mirada puesta en la seguridad. Soporta los principales "
"formatos de buzones: mbox o Maildir. Esta sección explica cómo configurar un "
"servidor imap o pop3."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:576(para)
msgid ""
"To install <application>dovecot</application>, run the following command in "
"the command prompt:"
msgstr ""
"Para instalar<application>dovecot</application>, ejecute la siguiente orden "
"en un terminal:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:581(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install dovecot-imapd dovecot-pop3d"
msgstr "sudo apt-get install dovecot-imapd dovecot-pop3d"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:586(para)
msgid ""
"To configure <application>dovecot</application>, you can edit the file "
"<filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename>. You can choose the protocol "
"you use. It could be pop3, pop3s (pop3 secure), imap and imaps (imap "
"secure). A description of these protocols is beyond the scope of this guide. "
"For further information, refer to the Wikipedia articles on <ulink "
"url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/POP3\">POP3</ulink> and <ulink "
"url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_Message_Access_Protocol\">IMAP</u"
"link>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:596(para)
msgid ""
"IMAPS and POP3S are more secure that the simple IMAP and POP3 because they "
"use SSL encryption to connect. Once you have chosen the protocol, amend the "
"following line in the file <filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"IMAPS y POP3S son más seguros que los simples IMAP y POP3 porque usan "
"encriptación SSL para conectarse. Una vez que elija el protocolo, corrija la "
"siguiente línea en el archivo <filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename>:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:602(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"protocols = pop3 pop3s imap imaps\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"protocols = pop3 pop3s imap imaps\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:605(para)
msgid ""
"Next, choose the mailbox you would like to use. "
"<application>Dovecot</application> supports <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">maildir</emphasis> and <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">mbox</emphasis> formats. These are the most commonly used "
"mailbox formats. They both have their own benefits and are discussed on "
"<ulink url=\"http://wiki.dovecot.org/MailboxFormat\">the Dovecot web "
"site</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:613(para)
msgid ""
"Once you have chosen your mailbox type, edit the file "
"<filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename> and change the following line:"
msgstr ""
"Una vez elegido su tipo de buzón de correo, edite el archivo "
"<filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename> y cambie la siguiente línea:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:618(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"mail_location = maildir:~/Maildir # (for maildir)\n"
"or\n"
"mail_location = mbox:~/mail:INBOX=/var/spool/mail/%u # (for mbox)\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"mail_location = maildir:~/Maildir # (para maildir)\n"
"or\n"
"mail_location = mbox:~/mail:INBOX=/var/spool/mail/%u # (para mbox)\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:624(para)
msgid ""
"You should configure your Mail Transport Agent (MTA) to transfer the "
"incoming mail to this type of mailbox if it is different from the one you "
"have configured."
msgstr ""
"Deberá configurar su Agente de Transporte de Correo (Mail Transport Agent, "
"MTA) para poder enviar el correo entrante a este tipo de buzón si resulta "
"ser distinto al que ha configurado."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:630(para)
msgid ""
"Once you have configured dovecot, restart the "
"<application>dovecot</application> daemon in order to test your setup:"
msgstr ""
"Una vez configurado dovecot, reinicie el demonio "
"<application>dovecot</application> para probar su configuración:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:635(para)
msgid ""
"If you have enabled imap, or pop3, you can also try to log in with the "
"commands <command>telnet localhost pop3</command> or <command>telnet "
"localhost imap2</command>. If you see something like the following, the "
"installation has been successful:"
msgstr ""
"Si usted ha habilitado imap, o pop3, usted puede probar conectarse con los "
"comandos <command>telnet localhost pop3</command> o <command>telnet "
"localhost imap2</command>. Si usted ve algo parecido a lo siguiente, la "
"instalación ha sido satisfactoria:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:642(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"bhuvan@rainbow:~$ telnet localhost pop3\n"
"Trying 127.0.0.1...\n"
"Connected to localhost.localdomain.\n"
"Escape character is '^]'.\n"
"+OK Dovecot ready.\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"bhuvan@rainbow:~$ telnet localhost pop3\n"
"Trying 127.0.0.1...\n"
"Connected to localhost.localdomain.\n"
"Escape character is '^]'.\n"
"+OK Dovecot ready.\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:651(title)
msgid "Dovecot SSL Configuration"
msgstr "Configuración de Dovecot SSL"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:652(para)
msgid ""
"To configure <application>dovecot</application> to use SSL, you can edit the "
"file <filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename> and amend following "
"lines:"
msgstr ""
"Para configurar <application>dovecot</application> para que utilice SSL, "
"usted puede editar el archivo <filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename> "
"y corregir las siguientes líneas:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:657(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"ssl_cert_file = /etc/ssl/certs/ssl-cert-snakeoil.pem\n"
"ssl_key_file = /etc/ssl/private/ssl-cert-snakeoil.key\n"
"ssl_disable = no\n"
"disable_plaintext_auth = no\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"ssl_cert_file = /etc/ssl/certs/ssl-cert-snakeoil.pem\n"
"ssl_key_file = /etc/ssl/private/ssl-cert-snakeoil.key\n"
"ssl_disable = no\n"
"disable_plaintext_auth = no\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:663(para)
msgid ""
"You can get the SSL certificate from a Certificate Issuing Authority or you "
"can create self signed SSL certificate. The latter is a good option for "
"email, because SMTP clients rarely complain about \"self-signed "
"certificates\". Please refer to <xref linkend=\"certificates-and-"
"security\"/> for details about how to create self signed SSL certificate. "
"Once you create the certificate, you will have a key file and a certificate "
"file. Please copy them to the location pointed in the "
"<filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename> configuration file."
msgstr ""
"Puede obtener el certificado SSL a través de una Autoridad emisora de "
"certificados o puede crear un certificado SSL autofirmado. Este último es "
"una buena opción para correo electrónico, ya que los clientes SMTP rara vez "
"se quejan por \"certificados autofirmados\". Por favor diríjase a <xref "
"linkend=\"certificates-and-security\"/> para obtener más detalles acerca de "
"cómo crear certificados SSL autofirmados. Una vez haya creado el "
"certificado, tendrá un archivo de clave y un archivo de certificado. "
"Cópielos a la ubicación indicada en el archivo de configuración "
"<filename>/etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf</filename>."

