#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:693(title) serverguide/C/mail.xml:771(title) serverguide/C/mail.xml:994(title)
msgid "Mailman"
msgstr "Mailman"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:694(para)
msgid ""
"Mailman is an open source program for managing electronic mail discussions "
"and e-newsletter lists. Many open source mailing lists (including all the "
"<ulink url=\"http://lists.ubuntu.com\">Ubuntu mailing lists</ulink>) use "
"Mailman as their mailing list software. It is powerful and easy to install "
"and maintain."
msgstr ""
"Mailman es un programa open source para gestionar discusiones de correo "
"electrónico y listas de noticias. Muchas listas de correo open source "
"(incluyendo todas las <ulink url=\"http://lists.ubuntu.com\">listas de "
"correo de Ubuntu</ulink>) usan Mailman como su software de gestión de "
"listas. Es potente y fácil de instalar y mantener."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:704(para)
msgid ""
"Mailman provides a web interface for the administrators and users. So, it "
"requires Apache with mod_perl support. Mailman uses an external mail server "
"to send and receive emails. It works perfectly with the following mail "
"servers:"
msgstr ""
"Mailman proporciona una interfaz web para el administrador y usuarios. Por "
"lo tanto, requiere Apache con soporte de mod_perl. Mailman usa un servidor "
"de correo externo para enviar y recibir correos electrónicos. Funciona "
"perfectamente con los siguientes servidores de correo:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:716(application)
msgid "Exim"
msgstr "Exim"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:719(application)
msgid "Sendmail"
msgstr "Sendmail"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:722(application)
msgid "Qmail"
msgstr "Qmail"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:727(para)
msgid ""
"We will see how to install and configure Mailman with, the Apache web "
"server, and either the Postfix or Exim mail server. If you wish to install "
"Mailman with a different mail server, please refer to the references section."
msgstr ""
"Veremos como instalar y configurar Mailman con, el servidor web Apache, y "
"cualquiera de los servidores de Correos Postfix o Exim. Si usted desea "
"instalar Mailman con un servidor de correos Diferente, por favor refiérase a "
"la sección de referencias."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:734(para)
msgid ""
"You only need to install one mail server and "
"<application>Postfix</application> is the default Ubuntu Mail Transfer Agent."
msgstr ""
"Solamente necesita instalar un servidor de correo y "
"<application>Postfix</application> es el agente de transferencia de correo "
"predeterminado de Ubuntu."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:739(title) serverguide/C/mail.xml:798(title)
msgid "Apache2"
msgstr "Apache2"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:740(para)
msgid ""
"To install apache2 you refer to <ulink url=\"./web-servers.xml#http-"
"installation\">HTTPD Installation</ulink> section for details."
msgstr ""
"Para instalar apache2 consulte la sección ulink url=\"./web-servers.xml#http-"
"installation\">Instalación de HTTPD</ulink> ."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:748(para)
msgid ""
"For instructions on installing and configuring Postfix refer to <xref "
"linkend=\"postfix\"/>"
msgstr ""
"Para conocer instrucciones sobre como instalar y configurar Postfix vea "
"<xref linkend=\"postfix\"/>"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:754(para)
msgid "To install Exim4 refer to <xref linkend=\"exim4\"/>."
msgstr "Para instalar Exim4 vea <xref linkend=\"exim4\"/>."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:765(application)
msgid "dc_use_split_config='true'"
msgstr "dc_use_split_config='true'"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:757(para)
msgid ""
"Once exim4 is installed, the configuration files are stored in the "
"<filename>/etc/exim4</filename> directory. In Ubuntu, by default, the exim4 "
"configuration files are split across different files. You can change this "
"behavior by changing the following variable in the "
"<filename>/etc/exim4/update-exim4.conf</filename> file: <placeholder-1/>"
msgstr ""
"Una vez instalado exmi4, los archivos de configuración son almacenados en el "
"directorio <filename>/etc/exim4</filename>. En Ubuntu, por defecto, los "
"archivos de configuración de exmi4 están divididos en archivos diferentes. "
"Usted puede cambiar este comportamiento cambiando la siguiente variable en "
"el archivo <filename>/etc/exim4/update-exim4.conf</filename>: <placeholder-"
"1/>"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:772(para)
msgid ""
"To install <application>Mailman</application>, run following command at a "
"terminal prompt:"
msgstr ""
"Para instalar <application>Mailman</application>, ejecute la siguiente orden "
"en una terminal:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:776(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install mailman"
msgstr "sudo apt-get install mailman"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:778(para)
msgid ""
"It copies the installation files in "
"<application>/var/lib/mailman</application> directory. It installs the CGI "
"scripts in <application>/usr/lib/cgi-bin/mailman</application> directory. It "
"creates <emphasis>list</emphasis> linux user. It creates the "
"<emphasis>list</emphasis> linux group. The mailman process will be owned by "
"this user."
msgstr ""
"Copia los archivos de instalación en el directorio "
"<application>/var/lib/mailman</application>. Instala los scripts CGI en el "
"directorio <application>/usr/lib/cgi-bin/mailman</application>. Crea el "
"usuario <emphasis>list</emphasis> en el sistema Linux. Crea el grupo "
"<emphasis>list</emphasis> en el sistema Linux. El proceso mailman tendrá "
"como propietario a ese usuario."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:790(para)
msgid ""
"This section assumes you have successfully installed "
"<application>mailman</application>, <application>apache2</application>, and "
"<application>postfix</application> or <application>exim4</application>. Now "
"you just need to configure them."
msgstr ""
"Esta sección supone que ha instalado correctamente los programas "
"<application>mailman</application>, <application>apache2</application> y "
"<application>postfix</application> (o <application>exim4</application>). "
"Ahora tan sólo necesita configurarlos."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:799(para)
msgid ""
"An example Apache configuration file comes with "
"<application>Mailman</application> and is placed in "
"<filename>/etc/mailman/apache.conf</filename>. In order for Apache to use "
"the config file it needs to be copied to <filename>/etc/apache2/sites-"
"available</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"Con <application>Mailman</application> se incluye un archivo de "
"configuración de ejemplo para Apache, que podrá encontrar en "
"<filename>/etc/mailman/apache.conf</filename>. Para que Apache pueda usar el "
"archivo de configuración, es necesario copiarlo a "
"<filename>/etc/apache2/sites-available</filename>:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:805(command)
msgid ""
"sudo cp /etc/mailman/apache.conf /etc/apache2/sites-available/mailman.conf"
msgstr ""
"sudo cp /etc/mailman/apache.conf /etc/apache2/sites-available/mailman.conf"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:807(para)
msgid ""
"This will setup a new Apache <emphasis>VirtualHost</emphasis> for the "
"Mailman administration site. Now enable the new configuration and restart "
"Apache:"
msgstr ""
"Esto configurará un nuevo Apache <emphasis>VirtualHost</emphasis> para la "
"administración del sitio de Mailman. Ahora habilite la nueva configuración y "
"reinicie Apache:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:812(command)
msgid "sudo a2ensite mailman.conf"
msgstr "sudo a2ensite mailman.conf"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:815(para)
msgid ""
"Mailman uses apache2 to render its CGI scripts. The mailman CGI scripts are "
"installed in the <application>/usr/lib/cgi-bin/mailman</application> "
"directory. So, the mailman url will be http://hostname/cgi-bin/mailman/. You "
"can make changes to the <filename>/etc/apache2/sites-"
"available/mailman.conf</filename> file if you wish to change this behavior."
msgstr ""
"Mailman usa apache2 para interpretar scripts CGI. Los scripts CGI de mailman "
"se instalan en el directorio <application>/usr/lib/cgi-"
"bin/mailman</application>. Así que el url de mailman será "
"http://hostname/cgi-bin/mailman/. Puede hacerle cambios al archivo  "
"<filename>/etc/apache2/sites-available/mailman.conf</filename> si desea "
"cambiar este comportamiento."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:826(para)
msgid ""
"For <application>Postfix</application> integration, we will associate the "
"domain lists.example.com with the mailing lists. Please replace "
"<emphasis>lists.example.com</emphasis> with the domain of your choosing."
msgstr ""
"Para integración de <application>Postfix</application>, necesitaremos "
"asociar el dominio lists.example.com con las listas de correo. Por favor "
"reemplace <emphasis>lists.example.com</emphasis> con el dominio de su "
"elección."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:830(para)
msgid ""
"You can use the postconf command to add the necessary configuration to "
"<filename>/etc/postfix/main.cf</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"Puede usar la orden postconf para añadir la configuración necesaria a "
"<filename>/etc/postfix/main.cf</filename>:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:834(command)
msgid "sudo postconf -e 'relay_domains = lists.example.com'"
msgstr "sudo postconf -e 'relay_domains = lists.example.com'"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:835(command)
msgid "sudo postconf -e 'transport_maps = hash:/etc/postfix/transport'"
msgstr "sudo postconf -e 'transport_maps = hash:/etc/postfix/transport'"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:836(command)
msgid "sudo postconf -e 'mailman_destination_recipient_limit = 1'"
msgstr "sudo postconf -e 'mailman_destination_recipient_limit = 1'"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:838(para)
msgid ""
"In <filename>/etc/postfix/master.cf</filename> double check that you have "
"the following transport:"
msgstr ""
"En <filename>/etc/postfix/master.cf</filename>, compruebe que tiene el "
"siguiente transporte:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:841(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"mailman   unix  -       n       n       -       -       pipe\n"
"  flags=FR user=list argv=/usr/lib/mailman/bin/postfix-to-mailman.py\n"
"  ${nexthop} ${user}\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"mailman   unix  -       n       n       -       -       pipe\n"
"  flags=FR user=list argv=/usr/lib/mailman/bin/postfix-to-mailman.py\n"
"  ${nexthop} ${user}\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:846(para)
msgid ""
"It calls the <emphasis>postfix-to-mailman.py</emphasis> script when a mail "
"is delivered to a list."
msgstr ""
"Éste llama al script <emphasis>postfix-to-mailman.py</emphasis> cuando se "
"envía un correo a una lista."

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:849(para)
msgid ""
"Associate the domain lists.example.com to the Mailman transport with the "
"transport map. Edit the file <filename>/etc/postfix/transport</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"Asocie el dominio listas.ejemplo.com a el transporte Mailman usando la "
"asociación de transporte. Edite el archivo "
"<filename>/etc/postfix/transport</filename>:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:852(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"lists.example.com      mailman:\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"listas.ejemplo.com      mailman:\n"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:855(para)
msgid ""
"Now have <application>Postfix</application> build the transport map by "
"entering the following from a terminal prompt:"
msgstr ""
"Ahora, haga que <application>Postfix</application> cree la asociación de "
"transporte escribiendo lo siguiente en un terminal:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:859(command)
msgid "sudo postmap -v /etc/postfix/transport"
msgstr "sudo postmap -v /etc/postfix/transport"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:861(para)
msgid "Then restart Postfix to enable the new configurations:"
msgstr "Entonces reinicie Postfix para habilitar las nuevas configuraciones:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:870(para)
msgid ""
"Once Exim4 is installed, you can start the Exim server using the following "
"command from a terminal prompt:"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se haya instalado Exim4, podrá arrancar el servidor Exim usando el "
"comando siguiente en un terminal:"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:886(para) serverguide/C/mail.xml:901(title)
msgid "Main"
msgstr "Principal"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:889(para) serverguide/C/mail.xml:941(title)
msgid "Transport"
msgstr "Transporte"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:892(para) serverguide/C/mail.xml:964(title)
msgid "Router"
msgstr "Enrutamiento"

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:877(para)
msgid ""
"In order to make mailman work with Exim4, you need to configure Exim4. As "
"mentioned earlier, by default, Exim4 uses multiple configuration files of "
"different types. For details, please refer to the <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.exim.org\">Exim</ulink> web site. To run mailman, we should "
"add new a configuration file to the following configuration types: "
"<placeholder-1/> Exim creates a master configuration file by sorting all "
"these mini configuration files. So, the order of these configuration files "
"is very important."
msgstr ""

#: serverguide/C/mail.xml:908(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"# start\n"
"# Home dir for your Mailman installation -- aka Mailman's prefix\n"
"# directory.\n"
"# On Ubuntu this should be \"/var/lib/mailman\"\n"
"# This is normally the same as ~mailman\n"
"MM_HOME=/var/lib/mailman\n"
"#\n"
"# User and group for Mailman, should match your --with-mail-gid\n"
"# switch to Mailman's configure script.  Value is normally \"mailman\"\n"
"MM_UID=list\n"
"MM_GID=list\n"
"#\n"
"# Domains that your lists are in - colon separated list\n"
"# you may wish to add these into local_domains as well\n"
"domainlist mm_domains=hostname.com\n"
"#\n"
"# -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=\n"
"#\n"
"# These values are derived from the ones above and should not need\n"
"# editing unless you have munged your mailman installation\n"
"#\n"
"# The path of the Mailman mail wrapper script\n"
"MM_WRAP=MM_HOME/mail/mailman\n"
"#\n"
"# The path of the list config file (used as a required file when\n"
"# verifying list addresses)\n"
"MM_LISTCHK=MM_HOME/lists/${lc::$local_part}/config.pck\n"
"# end\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"# comienzo\n"
"# Directorio de inicio para su instalación de Mailman -- el directorio "
"prefijo\n"
"# de Mailman.\n"
"# En Ubuntu debe ser \"/var/lib/mailman\"\n"
"# Normalmente, es lo mismo que ~mailman\n"
"MM_HOME=/var/lib/mailman\n"
"#\n"
